{\f0\fs28\b\cf1 Welcome to FloaTodo\cf0\b0\par}
{\f0\fs18\cf3 A keyboard-first, always-on-top task overlay for Windows\cf0\par}
\par

{\f0\fs20\b Quick Start\b0\par}
{\f0\fs18
FloaTodo lives on the right edge of your screen as a slim panel. It is always visible above all your other windows so your tasks are never more than a glance away.\par
\par
After installation, FloaTodo starts automatically and appears in your system tray (bottom-right of the taskbar). Look for the blue \b \u10003?\b0  icon.\par
}
\par

{\f0\fs20\b Show / Hide the Panel\b0\par}
{\f0\fs18
Press \b Ctrl + Shift + Space\b0  at any time \u8212? from any app \u8212? to toggle the panel. The same shortcut hides it when you\u8217?re done.\par
}
\par

{\f0\fs20\b Adding Tasks\b0\par}
{\f0\fs18
1.\tab Click the text field at the top (or press \b Ctrl+Shift+Space\b0  to open the panel \u8212? the field is auto-focused).\par
2.\tab Type a short task name and press \b Enter\b0  to add it instantly.\par
3.\tab For longer tasks with notes: type the title, then press \b Shift+Enter\b0  to expand into a full text area. Write as much as you need. Press \b Enter\b0  when done \u8212? the task opens in detail view automatically.\par
}
\par

